sql:
SELECT environment, AVG(CAST(storage AS INTEGER)) AS average_storage
FROM servers
GROUP BY environment;

SELECT user_id, COUNT(*) AS setting_change_count
FROM setting_history
GROUP BY user_id;

external_knowledge:
- "Treasure chests" metaphorically represent the memory capacity (in GB) of the servers;
- "Active ocean" refers to servers with 'active' status;
- "Development" indicates the environment type of the servers.
